AUDIO: 'digital twin of Earth, where you can explore around. Now, at the top here they have released a code and weights button, and if you click into it, here it says they are undergoing internal review, and they do plan to release the'

[20:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'models as well as the training data. For now, if you\'re interested in reading further, I\'ll link to this page in the description below. Now, at the beginning of the video, I mentioned that we have Terminator this week. I wasn\'t joking,'

[20:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so this AI is called Terminator, and no, it\'s not this Terminator, this one is actually really useful. Now, here\'s what it solves. You see, the problem with large reasoning models is that they usually overthink and they end up'

[21:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'spending a lot of tokens, and especially if you\'re paying for like API costs, then it\'s going to cost you a ton of money. A ton of these models just continue thinking and yapping all day and over explaining things. Most of the'

[21:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'time it\'s not actually necessary. So, what terminator does is this is a lightweight add-on which stops AI models from overthinking. It cuts off its reasoning once the answer is ready. So, here you can see that we are using Qwen'

[21:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '3 and on the left we are using this terminator add-on. It has already detected the final answer and it ends its response at 13.2 seconds, whereas on the right, if we don\'t add terminator,'

[21:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then it keeps thinking and yapping on and on and it takes like 76 seconds for this response to finish. So, this takes up a lot more time and uses a lot more tokens. So, here they say that terminator can cut reasoning length by'

[22:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'up to 55% and because it\'s terminating this early, it can like reduce the generation time by half. So, how this works is this is just an add-on. You don\'t need to train the base model'

[22:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'further. This is just a single-layer transformer probe that sits on top of existing models and it just detects when the final answer has been generated. It predicts a zero if the answer has not been generated or it outputs one if it'

[22:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'has. And if it has, then it basically terminates the response early. Now, especially if you\'re using Openclaw or other agentic systems which tend to keep yapping on and on, this terminator'

[22:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'add-on might be a good option to cut its responses early and reduce your costs. Now, unfortunately, they haven\'t released the code or the dataset to this. It says it\'s coming soon, so hopefully they will stick to their word'

